      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Salvatore Quasimodo (1901-1968) was an Italian author and poet.  He received the Nobel Prize for Literature in 1959.  For more information, see the Nobel Prize website's biography of him at <extref href="http://nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/literature/laureates/1959">http://nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/literature/laureates/1959</extref>.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Salvatore Quasimodo Manuscripts</emph> consists of drafts of two of his works, "La Tempesta" and "Elettra di Sofocle."</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
      <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
